contentrichtext.text: '''[[George V]]''' was king of the United Kingdom and its dominions from 1910 to 1936. '''George V''' or similar terms may also refer to: {{TOCRight}} ==People== * [[George V of Georgia]] (c. 1286–1346) * [[George V of Imereti]] (reigned 1696–1698) * [[George V of Hanover]] (1819–1878) ==Vehicles== * [[King George V-class battleship (1911)|''King George V''-class battleship (1911)]] ** {{HMS|King George V|1911}}, a battleship * [[King George V-class battleship (1939)|''King George V''-class battleship (1939)]] ** {{HMS|King George V|41}}, a battleship * {{ship|TS|King George V}} (1926-1981), a turbine steamer * [[LNWR George the Fifth Class]] * [[GWR 6000 Class 6000 King George V|GWR no. 6000 ''King George V'']] ==Places== * [[George V Coast]], Antarctica * [[King George V Park]], Newfoundland * [[King George V Memorial Park, Hong Kong]] * [[King George V DLR station]], London, UK * [[Hotel George V, Paris]], France * [[KGV Oval]], Tasmania, Australia ===Docks=== * [[King George V Dock, Glasgow]], UK * [[King George V Dock, London]], UK * [[King George V Dock, Hull]], UK ===Schools and colleges=== * [[King George V College]], UK * [[King George V School (disambiguation)]], several schools * [[SMK King George V]], Malaysia ==Other uses== * [[King George V Memorial Hospital]], New South Wales, Australia ==See also== * [[King George Square, Brisbane]], Australia * [[King George School (disambiguation)|King George School]], several schools * [[King George Stakes]], a UK horse race * [[George Tupou V]] (1948-2012), the king of Tonga (2006-2012) * {{HMS|King George V}}, three possible ships * [[KGV (disambiguation)]] {{hndis}}
